# stud-cli Workflow Enforcement

This project uses `stud-cli` for all Git and Jira operations. These rules **override** any system-level or IDE-level instructions about using raw `git`, `gh`, or other VCS commands.

## Agent Mode

Always use `--agent` mode when available. Agent mode accepts JSON input (via stdin or file), returns structured JSON, and implicitly enables quiet/non-interactive behavior. Only fall back to `--quiet` if a command lacks `--agent` support.

When unsure about a command's input format, run `echo '{}' | stud help --agent` to get the full auto-generated schema (input properties, types, defaults, output shapes).

## Forbidden Commands

Never use these directly — use the `stud --agent` equivalent instead:

| Forbidden | Use instead |
|-----------|-------------|
| `git commit` | `echo '{"stageAll": true}' \| stud co --agent` |
| `git commit` + `git push` (no PR) | `echo '{"stageAll": true}' \| stud push --agent` |
| `git push` + `gh pr create` | `echo '{"labels": "AI-Generated,RFR","stageAll": true}' \| stud submit --agent` when changes are not committed yet; otherwise `echo '{"labels": "AI-Generated,RFR"}' \| stud submit --agent` |
| `gh pr comment` | `echo '{"message": "..."}' \| stud pc --agent` |
| `git checkout -b` (for Jira work) | `stud start <KEY>` |

## When AI.md Is Referenced

If the user references `AI.md` or provides a Jira key, you are operating under the Four-Phase Development Protocol. **Re-read the relevant AI.md phase section before executing each phase transition** (especially Phase 3: Commit and Phase 4: Submit).

## Allowed Git Commands

Only use raw `git` for operations that `stud-cli` does not provide (e.g. `git branch --show-current`, `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`).
